snippet.title: Celebrities Who Exposed Amber Heard Because Of Her Lie!!!
snippet.description:
Amber Heard was got caught lying. Do you think she should deserve second chance. These celebrities caught her lying. Find out more about watching the video.


Famous film and television actress Amber Heard is being called out for lying on numerous occasions by various celebrities. One such celebrity is her ex-husband and Golden Globe winner Johnny Depp. ‚ÄúThe Pirates of the Caribbean‚Äù actor who sees himself drawn towards controversies and legal battles had once filed a 50 million defamation case against ex-wife Amber Heard at the time of their divorce. According to sources, the defamation case has witnessed some recent happenings wherein Depp and his team has issued a legal notice to Amber Heard‚Äôs ex-boyfriend and one of the richest space enthusiasts in the world, Elon Musk.
1- One of these well-wishers is Vanessa Paradis, the former partner of Johnny Depp who was the first celebrity to openly support Depp and expressed her doubts regarding Amber‚Äôs allegations in May 2020 wherein she accused Johnny of being extremely violent. She even supported Depp‚Äôs defamation case against Heard by issuing a statement. In that statement, she claimed that she has known Johnny for 25 years and has never faced a problem with him. She also stated that Johnny has always been a reverent and caring partner to her and a doting father to their two children. Vanessa also went on to call Amber‚Äôs allegations against Depp to be completely false and baseless.
2- Winona Ryder too, another former partner of Johnny Depp came forward to publish a declaration in support of him in the matter. Ryder clarified that Amber has been unreasonable with her allegations and the Johnny that she has known for so many years, is not even one percent close to what Amber falsely described him as. Winona has always considered him as his closest friend, more like family and thus, she knows him better than anyone else. This would make her the perfect person to testify in favor of Johnny since she knows that he is innocent and far from being violent or abusive.

Johnny Depp fans have not wasted a single minute to come out in support of their favourite star as soon as this controversy came into limelight. His fans tweeted that they cannot wait for Depp to get justice and strict action to be taken against Amber. Not only the fans, even celebrities and colleagues have shown their support to Johnny Depp, implying that they know him personally and he has never had wrong intentions. During the two-year marriage of Depp and Heard, Depp was often shown in bad light by the media but his well-wishers knew better and never left his side.
3- Sharon Osbourne is a celebrity who is known to have no filters in her mouth and speaks her heart out without any hesitation and fear of judgement. In an interview in November 2020, Sharon suggested that according to her, Amber should have been scrutinized and blamed equally by the media for this entire situation as a marriage is supposed to be a two-way street. She believed that Amber should stop playing the victim card even though she was at fault in numerous situations. Sharon also drew a comparison between the relationship of Johnny and Amber and her relationship with her husband Ozzy Osbourne.

So, will Johnny be able to prove that Amber has been lying all this while or is it ultimately both of them who are responsible for this chaos equally? Only time will tell.
That‚Äôs all for today. I hope you liked the video. If you did make sure to hit that like button and subscribe to the channel so that you never miss any amazing video from us.

snippet.description:

Here is the link to the deposition;
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-sKyN0_D_ec
As in my last video called, ‚ÄúA Therapist‚Äôs Thoughts on Johnny and Amber‚Äôs Audio Argument,‚Äù this deposition gives us a front row seat to watch things we are often talking about on this channel; how to know when someone is lying, does someone with narcissistic behaviors know when they are lying, and what is the difference between lies and delusional thinking?  We‚Äôll see how in the beginning she is lying, and then she shifts into her delusional narratives.  Delusional narratives are more confusing than lies, as the person is quite convinced of the ‚Äòtruth‚Äô in their narrative. snippet.title: Amber Heard claims Johnny Depp became 'monster' on drink and drugs then beat her  - News 247
snippet.description: became a ‚ÄúMonster‚Äù on drink and drugs, then beat, strangled and tormented his then-wife Amber Heard, she alleges in new court papers. ¬†The actress, who was married to Hollywood star for just over a year until she filed for divorce in May 2016, claims in horrific detail that Depp repeatedly hit her, pulled out her hair, choked and nearly suffocated. ¬†The allegations are made in a Virginia court filing in response to his ¬£38 million defamation lawsuit against her. ¬†Depp‚Äôs lawsuit relates to a 2018 piece written by Heard for the Washington Post in which she describes being the victim of domestic abuse but does not mention him in the article.   ¬†His lawsuit claims she insinuates he was the abuser and that Heard‚Äôs allegations are a ‚Äúhoax.‚Äù ¬†Heard, 32, has now responded by detailing numerous alleged incidents with Depp, 55, in court papers. ¬†She states she began dating the actor in early 2012, ‚ÄúAbout a year into our relationship, I began to witness Johnny abusing drugs and alcohol‚Ä¶ On some occasions, when Johnny simultaneously used both illegal narcotics and prescription medications I have had to get him medical attention. ¬†"Whenever he was using, I worried for both of us. Amber Heard is a world-renowned actress and an outspoken advocate for women's and children‚Äôs rights. Originally from Texas, she is an outspoken advocate for women's and children‚Äôs rights. She devotes her time off-screen to organizations like Amnesty International and Art of Elysium and most recently returned from a humanitarian trip to Jordan to visit Syrian refugees with the Syrian American Medical Society (SAMS).  Amber is our Human Rights Champion, lending her voice and support to promote the principles of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights, which was adopted 70 years ago.

snippet.title: Impeachment trial of President Trump | Jan. 29, 2020 (FULL LIVE STREAM)
snippet.description:
House impeachment managers and President Trump‚Äôs lawyers have concluded their opening arguments in the Senate. The impeachment trial moves into the question period for both sides on Jan. 29, when senators submit questions in writing to Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. The chief justice will read questions out loud, alternating between the majority and minority for up to eight hours. 

Trump was impeached by the House of Representatives in December for abuse of power and obstruction of Congress. Impeachment does not mean that the president has been removed from office. In the next phase, the Senate must hold a trial to make that determination. A Senate impeachment trial has happened only two other times in American history and once in the modern era. At the center of the Democrats‚Äô case is that Trump sought to withhold military assistance and an Oval Office meeting until Ukraine announced investigations into former vice president Joe Biden and his son.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Arrives for Trial Against Newspaper That Accused Him of Abusing Ex-wife Amber Heard
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp is expected to wrap up his evidence Monday at his libel trial against a tabloid newspaper that accused him of abusing ex-wife Amber Heard.

The Hollywood star is suing News Group Newspapers, publisher of The Sun, and the paper‚Äôs executive editor, Dan Wootton, over an April 2018 article that called him a ‚Äúwife-beater.‚Äù

Depp is in the witness box at the High Court in London for a fifth day - two days longer than scheduled - in a case that has exposed a bitter rift between the estranged spouses.

Depp, 57, and Heard, 34, met on the set of the 2011 comedy ‚ÄúThe Rum Diary‚Äù and married in Los Angeles in February 2015. Heard, a model and actress, filed for divorce the following year, and the divorce was finalized in 2017.

Under cross-examination by The Sun‚Äôs lawyer, Sasha Wass, Depp depicted a tumultuous relationship with Heard during a period when he was trying to kick drugs and alcohol, and sometimes lapsing.

He called the relationship ‚Äúa crime scene waiting to happen.‚Äù But he denied hitting Heard and accused her of compiling a dossier of fake claims against him as an ‚Äúinsurance policy.‚Äù

snippet.title: Andrew Golden Full Length Deposition - Arkansas School Shooter
snippet.description:
Full Length Deposition of Andrew Golden, Westside, Arkansas Middle School Shooting

In the early afternoon of March 24, 1998, two students from Westside Middle School, located approximately two miles west of Jonesboro (Craighead County), conducted an armed ambush on teachers and students, which resulted in five dead and ten others injured. The shooters, Andrew Golden and Mitchell Johnson, were arrested and prosecuted for the crime. The incident was one of two school shootings in Arkansas and one of several school shootings across the nation that adjusted school administrators‚Äô and law enforcement officers‚Äô concepts on school security and response plans to violent incidents at schools.

The students and teachers had returned from spring break the day before the shooting. Fifth period was just starting at 12:35 p.m. when a fire alarm caused the student body and faculty to evacuate the building. This alarm was triggered by eleven-year-old Andrew Golden, who, shortly after activating the alarm, joined thirteen-year-old Mitchell Johnson in a field adjacent to the school. This location had a clear view of the exit doors used during a fire drill. At 12:41 p.m., as eighty-seven students and nine teachers evacuated the building, Golden and Johnson began firing at the group with various weapons, including handguns and semi-automatic and bolt action rifles. In rapid succession, Golden and Johnson fired thirty rounds at the group.

Sixth-grade teacher Shannon Wright was killed, along with four students: Natalie Brooks (age eleven), Paige Ann Herring (age twelve), Stephanie Johnson (age twelve), and Brittheny Varner (age eleven). Nine students and another teacher, Lynette Thetford, were injured. Among the wounded students were Candice Porter (age eleven), who reportedly dated and broke up with Johnson, and Jennifer Jacobs (age twelve), who reportedly dated and broke up with Golden prior to the shooting. Although some speculated the suspects targeted specific students or teachers based upon past interactions, this theory was never proven and the victims‚Äô association to the suspects was eventually considered coincidental. After firing upon the crowd, both suspects fled through the woods and were apprehended by the police without further violence.

The police discovered that the boys were attempting to make their way back to a van parked almost half a mile away from the school. This van, taken from Johnson‚Äôs residence, contained food, extra clothing, and camping equipment to facilitate their escape. An investigation by the police determined that three handguns were taken from Golden‚Äôs residence and an additional four handguns and three rifles came from Golden‚Äôs grandfather‚Äôs residence. The Craighead County Sheriff‚Äôs Office assumed responsibility for the investigation of the incident and charged both suspects with five counts of capital murder and ten counts of first-degree battery.

By all accounts, the two suspects were not close friends. In fact, with Johnson attending the seventh grade and Golden attending the sixth grade, the students only shared bus rides to and from school. But both verbalized hostility toward others and threatened that something big was about to happen. Johnson lived with his mother and stepfather, and had a difficult relationship with his father. Fellow students reported that Johnson was bullish and bragged about being in a gang. Within the same school year as the shooting, Johnson was assigned in-school suspension three times and was criminally charged for molesting a two-year-old girl. In contrast to Johnson‚Äôs overt behavioral problems, Golden led a kind of ‚ÄúJekyll and Hyde‚Äù lifestyle. Golden was not a disciplinary problem at school and was regarded by many adults as a well-mannered and cheerful student. He was very close to his family and shared the family‚Äôs interest in firearms by competing and winning marksmanship awards. However, apparently unbeknownst to his family, Golden reportedly demonstrated violence by firing his BB gun at animals and other children.

snippet.title: Elizabeth Holmes exposed: the $9 billion medical ‚Äòmiracle‚Äô that never existed | 60 Minutes Australia

Elizabeth Holmes promised the world a medical revolution. At 19, she claimed to have invented a miniaturised machine that with a single drop of blood could map a person‚Äôs health quickly, reliably and cheaply. She boasted that her technology meant serious diseases like cancer would be prevented before they happened. And it was not only a ‚Äúwow‚Äù moment for patients. High-profile investors rushed to pour a fortune into Holmes‚Äô company, Theranos, and she became Silicon Valley‚Äôs first self-made female billionaire. But as Tara Brown reports, her invention was an invention ‚Äì it simply didn‚Äôt work. Elizabeth Holmes is no visionary. She‚Äôs a cruel fraudster who has put people‚Äôs lives at risk, and because of that, now faces 20 years in jail.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Ordered To Sit For Deposition In $50M Amber Heard Defamation Case
snippet.description:
After months of slipping out of having to actually sit down for the $50 million defamation lawsuit that he launched against¬†Amber Heard,¬†Johnny Depp¬†may have run out of moves.

‚ÄúPlaintiff John C. Depp, II shall ‚Ä¶appear for three successive days in counsel for Defendant‚Äôs offices in Virginia ‚Ä¶or at such other place in Northern Virginia designated by counsel for Defendant, from November 10-12, 2020, beginning at 10:00 a.m. each day,‚Äù declares an order yesterday from Fairfax County VA Circuit Court Chief Judge Bruce White 

No word yet from the Depp camp if the¬†Fantastic Beasts¬†star plans to fight this order, yet. However, if the Oscar nominee does show up, it looks like it will involve him having to skip out of some of the UK filming of the latest sequel in the WB franchise from J.K Rowling.

It was the coronavirus delayed start of shooting on the David Yates-directed¬†Fantastic Beasts 3¬†that was why Depp sought in August to have the commencement of the trial in the contentious
matter pushed back to mid-2021 and why he has been supposedly unable to sit with Heard‚Äôs lawyers previously. Though the actor has been conducting a mini-grand tour of European film festivals the last month or so, WB SVP for Corporate Legal Wayne M. Smith wrote in a September 8 letter that ‚Äúwe require Mr. Depp to be in the United Kingdom from September 17 through the anticipated end of production in mid-February, 2021.‚Äù

Citing the backlogs COVID-19 has caused in the courts, Judge White¬†on September 11¬†shoved the previously much delayed trial from its anticipated January 2021 start to May 3 next year. Under that timeline, Depp‚Äôs deposition desired dates would have taken place mere weeks before the trial began ‚Äì a state of affairs that Heard‚Äôs attorneys claim gave them little time.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Gets Elon Musk‚Äôs Help Testifying Against Amber Heard?!
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp Gets Elon Musk‚Äôs Help Testifying Against Amber Heard?!

WATCH NEXT üëáüèª

James Franco Reacts To Being Subpoenaed By Johnny‚Äôs Legal Team‚Ä¶

Elon Musk Wants to SUPPORT Johnny Depp By Testifying Against Amber in 2022

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IQc-w9hgVv8

Elon Musk Set To Testify Against Amber Heard & Defend Johnny Depp

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A5xAuPZaoI8

Divorce is never easy, and when it comes to celebrity divorce, public attention is added to the whole nightmare that follows the process. Of course, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard‚Äôs split is certainly no exception. Even though their legal battle has already lasted years, there's a little chance that new participants of the case, like Tesla CEO Elon Musk and actor James Franco, end up testifying in the court case against Amber Heard?
According to court documents obtained by Us Weekly, James Franco and Elon Musk were subpoenaed on October 26, 2021. They were ordered to ‚Äúproduce the books, record, electronically stored information and tangible things designated and described‚Äù ‚Äî including ‚Äúverbal conversations, telephone calls, letters, emails, memoranda and reports‚Äù ‚Äî by January 17, 2022. As we have already spoken in details about James Franco being dragged to the case in the previous video (if you haven‚Äôt seen it, you definitely should), in this episode we are going to reveal all the details about Elon Musk‚Äôs who once challenged Johnny Depp to a cage fight. 
Johnny Depp‚Äôs legal team is interested in speaking with Elon Mus kand James Franco because they may have a really important information that can help the case going. Here is an official Adam Waldman‚Äôs (JD‚Äôs lawyer) statement: ‚ÄúWe are interested in James Franco and Elon Musk as fact witnesses because we have evidence they are men who saw Amber Heard‚Äôs face in the days and nights between when she claimed Mr. Depp smashed her in the face on May 21 and when she went to court with painted on ‚Äòbruises‚Äô to obtain temporary restraining order on May 27‚Äù.
The Tesla billionaire Elon Musk has been involved in Johnny Depp and Amber Heard‚Äôs case once again and this time around his connection to Amber/Johnny drama is a little bit different than previously. snippet.title: Macrophage Infection by HIV: Implications for Pathogenesis and Cure: Day One
snippet.description:
The National Institute of Mental Health (NIMH) and the Ragon Institute of MGH, MIT, and Harvard conducted a virtual meeting, Macrophage Infection by HIV: Implications for Pathogenesis and Cure, from October 13-14, 2021. While CD4+ T cells are the main targets of HIV infection, macrophages also become infected and resist the cytopathic effects of infection, contributing to HIV reservoir persistence. Furthermore, they drive inflammation and can contribute to the development of co-morbidities, including HIV-associated CNS dysfunction.

This meeting examined emerging data related to macrophage interactions with the immune system during HIV infection, macrophage reservoirs and approaches to their elimination, and the involvement of CNS myeloid reservoirs and associated co-morbidities. The meeting also highlighted recent work on macrophage inflammation in the context of SARS-CoV-2 infection and work from new NIMH-funded investigators. A panel discussed research gaps and priorities related to human macrophage reservoirs and inflammation/co-morbidities, and treatment strategies for HIV remission and cure.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp granted access to view Amber Heard's phone
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp has been granted access to Amber Heard's phone.
The 'Pirates of the Caribbean' actor is suing his ex-wife for libel and has claimed she doctored photos to make it look like he had assaulted her, and so a court has now agreed to his request for lawyers to examine her mobile use as he wants to prove his forgery claim.
His lawyer, Benjamin Chew, said: "Ms Heard‚Äôs counsel has repeatedly used these phony photographs at deposition.‚Äù 
The lawyer also claimed Los Angeles police had "disavowed the photographs‚Äù and ‚Äúdid not depict what they saw‚Äù.
He added: "[Police] found no injury upon Ms. Heard and no disruption to the penthouses. 
‚ÄúMs. Heard and her friends then fabricated photos that she used to obtain an ex parte TRO [temporary restraining order] and a $7 million divorce settlement which Ms. Heard falsely testified in London she gave to the ACLU and, more scandalously, to the Children‚Äôs Hospital of Los Angeles; sick children with cancer."
The lawyer had argued earlier images handed over had no metadata so their expert, Brian Neumeister, could not verify the details.
The lawyer said: "Mr. Neumeister‚Äôs preliminary investigation shows that a number of the photographs have been run through a photo ‚Äî a photo editing application called Photo 3 that can easily manipulate images such as showing bruises where none actually existed."
And he insisted in last year's libel trial with The Sun newspaper - who Johnny unsuccessfully sued after they branded him a "wife beater" - the publication's own expert concluded photos allegedly depicting the 'Danish Girl' star's 2015 injuries were "manipulated three years later".
He added: ‚ÄúAs such, any editing of the trial bundle versions would have been on or after Oct. 6 2018.
‚ÄúSo Ms. Heard or someone on her behalf doctored those photographs three years later. When that came up in her testimony in London, Ms. Heard falsely denied it. In short, Your Honour, without forensic imaging Mr. Neumeister cannot properly assess or verify Ms. Heard‚Äôs data."
An expert will now be able to look at the phone to examine if the photos had been fabricated, but the judge denied a request from the 'Aquaman' actress' team to have Johnny hand over his phone and laptop, saying they had asked for "too broad" a search.
Amber's lawyers have hit back and accused the 58-year-old star of failing to support the "authenticity" of his own evidence.
Her attorney said: ‚ÄúAmber Heard remains willing and able to support the authenticity of her evidence, and her IT forensics expert has cooperated in this effort.
"In sharp contrast, Mr Depp has been unable to produce even the audio tapes from which he leaked a partial out-of-context portion, much less any support for the authenticity of any of his evidence.‚Äù
The lawsuit relates to a December 2019 op-ed Amber penned for the Washington Post, in which the 35-year-old star wrote she had ‚Äúbecome a public figure representing domestic abuse", though she didn't mention her ex-husband by name.
The suit claims the 'Black Mass' star has suffered financial losses as a result of the accusations.

snippet.title: Aquaman 2: Amber Heard Shares Excitement For Controversial Return in DCEU Sequel
snippet.description:
Aquaman 2: Amber Heard Shares Excitement For Controversial Return in DCEU Sequel

The DC Extended Universe is quickly ramping up a massive, new slate of projects that are set to release over the next couple of years starting off with Wonder Woman 1984, which hopes to debut in theaters before the end of 2020. Amongst other exciting sequels and debut franchises will be the much anticipated Aquaman 2 continuing on from 2018's Aquaman, which became the highest-grossing DCEU movie to date and the first to cross $1 billion at the global box office.

Information regarding this sequel is scarce at the moment due to its release being over two years away, although James Wan is confirmed to return as the director. The film's starring actor Jason Momoa will additionally be taking on writing duties with David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick as he suits up for his fourth appearance as the King of Atlantis, and he will serve as an executive producer on the film as well.

More news has arrived on another star from the first movie to confirm her return for the sequel, even though it comes alongside some major controversy.

In a new interview with Entertainment Weekly, DC Extended Universe star Amber Heard confirmed that she will return as Mera for the upcoming untitled Aquaman sequel. Heard also revealed that the film is hoping to start on production sometime next year, and she said

"I'm super excited about the amount of fan love and the amount of fan appreciation that Aquaman has acquired and that it has garnered so much excitement for Aquaman and Mera that it means we'll be coming back. I'm so excited to film that."

This news arrives following reports that Heard was included as a part of the reshoots for the Snyder Cut of Justice League. It also comes in the midst of an ongoing legal battle with her ex-husband Johnny Depp, which has led to petitions for her removal from the movie and has been signed by over 1 million people this far.

Even though actor's off-screen lives usually don't factor too much into studio decisions on casting, as is usually the case with fan petitions, this is an extremely interesting case considering the circumstances of Amber Heard's legal situation at the moment. The UK courts recently ruled in her favor against Johnny Depp, even considering the mountain of evidence that she may have been the one in the wrong, and the cries from fans to see her replaced as Mera in the DCEU have been overwhelming.

Nevertheless, Heard seems excited and grateful to be a part of the upcoming Aquaman sequel, which is currently in its earliest stages of development. She joins Jason Momoa and Patrick Wilson as the only confirmed cast members to return for the sequel, which is set to expand mightily on the world beneath the ocean waves. The central plot of Aquaman 2 will explore the far reaches of the other Seven Kingdoms of Atlantis, and it will be exciting to find out more details as they come.

The untitled Aquaman sequel is hopeful to begin production in 2021 as it prepares for worldwide release on December 16, 2022.

snippet.title: Contempt Charge for Royce Toney, a No Show in Divorce Suit Deposition
snippet.description:
january 2011

Today Sheriff Royce Toney was supposed to speak out about the divorce suit where his name appears in‚Äîduring a scheduled deposition.

But Sheriff Toney stood up the divorce attorney for the other side by not showing up to the deposition‚Äînow attorney Laurie Burkett slapped Sheriff Toney with a rule of contempt and other penalties, according to court documents obtained by NBC 10.

Back in early December, businessman Larry Culp alleged that his wife, Laurie, and Sheriff Royce Toney had a secret sexual affair that lasted two years, according to a divorce petition.

On Jan. 21, Royce Toney was scheduled for a deposition at attorney Laurie Burkett's law office in Monroe, but he was a no-show.

Additionally, an attorney asked Sheriff Toney to bring bills, photos, and videotapes, which would support allegations that the affair happened in a variety of places, including the sheriff's personal office, the Rifle Range, and the sheriff's office's training facility.

Royce Toney's attorney, Brian Crawford, told NBC 10 that the sheriff didn't appear at the deposition because a judge hasn't ruled on previous motions and protective orders related to the case.

On January 7, the date both sides were scheduled to a hearing to determine whether the deposition would occur in the first place. But the sheriff's attorney says it had to be postponed because Laurie Burkett was sick.

Crawford says Sheriff Toney would comply with a subpoena, as long as a judge determines there is a legal basis for the sheriff to testify.

In the rule of contempt attorney Laurie Burkett filed today, it states, "It is clear that Royce Toney believes he can do whatever he wants in defiance of the court's orders."

Burkett is asking that Sheriff Toney be found in contempt, and to reimburse Larry Culp for attorney's fees, and costs for violating the subpoena.

Burkett is also asking that Royce Toney appear in court in front of a judge Feb. 15, to show why he shouldn't be found in contempt for disobeying a court order.

Ouachita Parish Sheriff's Deputy Scott Smith is also ordered to appear in Burkett's office to testify Jan. 28 next week.

snippet.title: Drake Bell Sentencing
snippet.description:
Jared Drake Bell, the 34-year-old actor best known for his leading role on the 2000s Nickelodeon series Drake and Josh, has been charged with a felony in Ohio over an alleged inappropriate ‚Äúrelationship‚Äù with a teenage girl.

According to the Cuyahoga County Prosecutor‚Äôs Office, the teen was 15 years old at the time of the alleged Dec. 2017 incident. She filed a report with her local police department in Canada in Oct. 2018. This report regarded an incident that allegedly happened the year before at a nightclub in Cleveland, Ohio.

‚ÄúCanadian authorities contacted the Cleveland Division of Police who conducted a subsequent investigation,‚Äù said prosecutor‚Äôs office spokesman Tyler Sinclair in an email to Law&Crime. ‚ÄúThat investigation revealed that the victim, who had established a relationship with Bell several years prior, attended his concert in December 2017. While there, Bell violated his duty of care and, in doing so, created a risk of harm to the victim. The investigation also revealed that months leading up to the concert, Bell sent the victim inappropriate social media messages.‚Äù

In addition to being an actor, Bell is a musician.

Bell pleaded not guilty at his arraignment on Thursday. The defendant is charged with attempted endangering children (a felony), and disseminating matter harmful to juveniles (a misdemeanor).

Bell‚Äôs attorney Ian Friedman indicated that all facts will be revealed in court, but he has no additional comment, said a statement from law firm Friedman & Nemecek.

Ex-girlfriend Melissa Lingafelt said last year that Bell was verbally and physically abusive.

He denied wrongdoing.

‚ÄúAs our relationship ended ‚Äî more than a decade ago ‚Äî we, unfortunately, both called each other terrible names, as often happens when couples are breaking up,‚Äù Bell said in a statement to People. ‚ÄúBut that is it.‚Äù

#DrakeBell

Les Mis√©rables (/le…™ Àåm…™z…ôÀàr…ëÀêb…ôl, -bl…ô/, French: [le mize Åabl(…ô)]) is a French historical novel by Victor Hugo, first published in 1862, that is considered one of the greatest novels of the 19th century.

In the English-speaking world, the novel is usually referred to by its original French title. However, several alternatives have been used, including The Miserables, The Wretched, The Miserable Ones, The Poor Ones, The Wretched Poor, The Victims and The Dispossessed. Beginning in 1815 and culminating in the 1832 June Rebellion in Paris, the novel follows the lives and interactions of several characters, particularly the struggles of ex-convict Jean Valjean and his experience of redemption.

Examining the nature of law and grace, the novel elaborates upon the history of France, the architecture and urban design of Paris, politics, moral philosophy, antimonarchism, justice, religion, and the types and nature of romantic and familial love. Les Mis√©rables has been popularized through numerous adaptations for film, television and the stage, including a musical.

snippet.title: Joe Exotic Deposition   Bunny   Litigation IQ
snippet.description:
For an analysis of Joe's Deposition mistakes, read this blog post: https://www.litigationiq.com/post/joe-exotic-deposition-what-not-to-do

Witness Preparation
Deposition Mistakes: Joe's demeanor is unprofessional. He rubs his face and appears to be annoyed. This type of nonverbal communication is usually a turnoff for jurors. 
He stretches then rubs the back of his neck, which signals to opposing counsel that he's tired, disengaged, and his guard is down (i.e., time to attack). It also looks unprofessional.
Joe looks at his own attorney while answering, which jurors often interpret as "looking for the answer," or "looking for cues." 
Joe's answers in this clip are bad. He's asked whether the lawsuit was already pending at the time he distributed photographs (the topic at issue in the copyright case). He agrees by saying "yeah." Next, opposing counsel inserts the premise that Joe was aware Big Cat Rescue didn't authorize the use of the photographs, to which Joe agrees. Joe then tries to outwit the attorney and somehow dodge liability by saying "yeah, except I didn't make these." But then the attorney gets Joe to admit that he participated in the demonstration and handed out the photos. Joe then denies handing out the photos because he was "the one in the bunny suit." The whole sequence is messy, contains contradictory testimony, and would likely annoy a jury.


Click here for a compilation of Roger Stone's Unhinged Greatest Hits https://youtu.be/J2dV93B3Pe4

snippet.title: Clip #3 Katherine Morris Death Investigation - Missing Surveillance Footage - Chief Lyle Deposition
snippet.description:
Clip # 3  The Katherine Sarah Morris Death Investigation - gone wrong.   

If you don't get the significance - this video was made in 2013. PROOF that for 6 years several Anne Arundel County police officers would lie to the Morris family and the public about why there are missing pieces of the surveillance footage of the death scene of Kathy Morris. But why? Please share this and stay tuned for more!

A mother becomes private investigator and civil rights advocate following the mishandling of her daughters death investigation. The night Katherine dies her car was under the auspices of four surveillance camera's in a busy well traveled mall parking lot on a Saturday night, from approx 6 p.m. on May 5, 2012 to about 8 a.m. May 6, 2012 . From the night of May 5, 2012 the family is only given the footage from the camera that is the farthest away from the car. The mother views the footage she is given and finds that it appears to have been tampered with. When questioned in 2012 the police will claim the missing footage is because the footage would not play because of system incompatibilities.  Then for five additional years (from 2013 to 2018) they will tell the family and the public (including the FBI) that cameras were motion sensitive so there was no footage because there was no movement in the parking lot where Katherine's body is found.  Then in October of 2018 the Chief of Police Timothy Altomare states the missing video was deleted but offers no further explanation.  Where does the truth start and where does it end?  This video has been edited for time and is the deposition of Chief Gary Lyle a 27 year veteran of the Anne Arundel County Police Department with a background in special investigations. He is being deposed under oath by the mother of the victim, Marguerite Morris who is becoming a well known advocate calling for greater police accountability and transparency.  The full length unedited version is available on youtube.  So what happened out there and when will someone on the police force speak up?  Do all ares concerning black lives matter?  Recently the Chief of Police Altomare is caught on camera during a public hearing appearing to wink and smile at the States Attorney as the Rev. Marguerite Morris comes forward to ask a question as if her efforts are an inside joke.  Whats that about?  During this same public hearing Chief Altomare says any officer found to be untruthful will be without a job.  Really?  Do black lives really matter in Anne Arundel County Maryland? No call for accountability - there will be no change.  I know I am not alone.  Got a story email forkathyssake@gmail.com  Want to help?  Visit forkathyssake.com and donate.

snippet.title: Deposition Misconduct by Attorney Witness
snippet.description:
Deposition of Colorado Attorney Robert E. Abrams, March 12, 2018.

http://www.coloradosupremecourt.com/pdj/Decisions/Abrams,%20Conditional%20Admission%20of%20Misconduct,%2020PDJ004,%2004-30-20.pdf

People v. Robert E. Abrams. 20PDJ004. April 30, 2020.

The Presiding Disciplinary Judge approved the parties‚Äô amended conditional admission of misconduct and suspended Robert E. Abrams (attorney registration number 37950) for one year, 90 days to be served and nine months to be stayed upon the successful completion of a two-year period of probation. The suspension took effect May 14, 2020.

Abrams committed several discrete types of misconduct in connection with his corporate representation and defense in litigation of three individuals and a corporate entity. Abrams‚Äôs continued representation of his clients, the defendants, after he was personally named as a co-defendant in the same action created a conflict of interest. He did not secure informed written consent from his clients authorizing him to continue with the representation despite the conflict.

In the same case, Abrams filed written discovery responses that violated a trial court order specifically prohibiting the parties from using ad hominem attacks, sarcastic or bombastic rhetoric, or any language that did not conform to the norms of civil discourse. Further, Abrams repeatedly disrupted his own deposition and prematurely ended the session after less than thirty minutes; the court-appointed special master then had to review the transcript, issue an order sanctioning Abrams, and personally preside over Abrams‚Äôs second deposition.

During lunch break on the second day of trial, Abrams went to opposing counsel‚Äôs office building with no legitimate reason for being in the building at that time. He rode the elevator with opposing counsel and his client (the plaintiff in the case), over objections from opposing counsel and a security guard. Abrams was disruptive to and confrontational with people in opposing counsel‚Äôs office. Based on this conduct, the trial court entered a restraining order against Abrams, listing opposing counsel as the protected party.

Finally, Abrams recklessly and falsely submitted to the court an affidavit that contained inaccurate information.

Through this conduct, Abrams violated Colo. RPC 1.7(a)(2) (a lawyer shall not represent a client if the representation will be materially limited by the lawyer‚Äôs responsibilities to another client or by the lawyer‚Äôs personal interests); Colo. RPC 3.4(c) (a lawyer shall not knowingly disobey an obligation under the rules of a tribunal); Colo. RPC 8.4(c) (providing that it is professional misconduct for a lawyer to engage in conduct involving dishonesty,
fraud, deceit, or misrepresentation); and Colo. RPC 8.4(d) (providing that it is professional misconduct for a lawyer to engage in conduct prejudicial to the administration of justice).

The case file is public per C.R.C.P. 251.31.

snippet.title: Kyle Rittenhouse breaks down crying while on stand in Kenosha homicide trial
snippet.description:
In dramatic courtroom testimony, Kyle Rittenhouse, the teenager who fatally shot two people in August 2020 during unrest in Kenosha, Wis., recounted the first deadly shooting.

Until he began crying, Rittenhouse had been recounting his steps leading up to the moments he opened fire. Rittenhouse also described his prior encounters with Joseph Rosenbaum, the first man he shot, saying that Rosenbaum had been screaming threats at Rittenhouse and others on the streets that night.

Legal experts have said the case effectively boils down to whether jurors believe his self-defense claims, which makes his testimony crucial. Jurors will weigh whether they agree Rittenhouse believed he feared for his safety or life, and his testimony provides them a key window into what he says went through his mind each time he pulled the trigger. snippet.title: Johnny Depp Can No Longer Put Off Deposition in Defamation Case Against Amber Heard
snippet.description: The 'Pirates of the Caribbean' actor has been ordered by a judge to make time for a sit-down with his former wife's lawyers while he's filming his latest 'fantastic Beasts' movie.   Oct 18, 2020  ¬†AceShowbiz - Johnny Depp has been ordered to sit for a deposition in his defamation case against ex-wife Amber Heard.  ¬† Fairfax County, Virginia Circuit Court Chief Judge Bruce White has told the "Pirates of the Caribbean" star he can no longer put off a sit down with the actress' lawyers, insisting he should appear for "three successive days" at a venue to be decided by Heard's legal team "from November 10-12, 2020, beginning at 10.00am each day."  ¬† The ruling follows a request from Heard's attorneys, insisting they needed to speak with Depp "on or before October 30, 2020" to give them enough time to plan their defence before the rescheduled trial date in May (21).  ¬† Depp previously cited his commitments to filming the latest "Fantastic Beasts" movie in the U.K. as his reason for delaying ...

snippet.title: Why Amber Heard Donated $7 Million Divorce Settlement From Johnny Depp
snippet.description: Amber Heard is giving away every cent of her $7 million divorce settlement. The actress, who filed for divorce from Johnny Depp, said she is giving half the money to the American Civil Liberties Union for its violence against women campaign. The other half will go to the Children's Hospital of Los Angeles. snippet.title: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard Is OFFICIALLY The Worst Split In Hollywood After THIS..
snippet.description:
Let‚Äôs face it. Divorces are not only hard for the people involved, but are also messy, time consuming, and are pretty darn expensive. Especially if the divorcees are both huge people, there will be tons of dollars involved. But of all the messy divorces in the history of the entertainment industry, there will surely always be a couple that would dominate the list. From the scandalous split of Real Housewives of Beverly Hills cast Erika Jayne and her lawyer husband Tom Gerardi, to the heartbreaking separations of all time couple favorite Brad Pitt and Angelina Jolie, down to big industry names like Yolanda Hadid and David Foster, celebrity divorces are usually messy. And more often than not, they take up headlines for weeks. However, if there are two big names dominating the world of the ugliest divorces in Hollywood today, there might be no one else that may top off Johnny Depp and Amber Heard‚Äôs divorce, which consequences are still being faced in an ongoing lawsuit up to this day. So of all these chaotic celebrity divorces, where do you think Amber Heard and Johnny Depp‚Äôs situation fall down? Is their situation really topsy turvy enough to top the worst couples who got divorced? Let‚Äôs find the answer to that in this video. But before anything else, make sure first to hit that subscribe button and smash that notification bell for more updates on Johnny Depp and Amber Heard‚Äôs lawsuit case, and some other divorces that are dominating the internet today. Now, let‚Äôs dig in!

First, to be able to determine if Johnny and Amber‚Äôs messy marriage and divorce really does qualify to top this roster of the ugliest Hollywood divorces, let‚Äôs go back to the very beginning. Johnny Depp has been in the height of his career in the industry for many, many years now. This helped Johnny begin his acting career, landing more minor roles and then major ones. He also played a few roles with Helena Bonham Carter in many Tim Burton films such as Charlie and the Chocolate Factory, Alice in Wonderland and Alice Through the Looking Glass, Corpse Bride, Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street, and Dark Shadows. One of the most widely-known appearances of Johnny Depp that perhaps brought him the largest commercial and critical success was the Disney media franchise ‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean‚Äù series, where he landed and reprised his lead role for all five movies that ran from 2003 to 2017.

Amber Heard, on the other hand, started her acting career in 2003, first by appearing in two music videos, and then later on landing small supporting roles in three various television series. This then later on elevated her to more film and television roles, both supporting and lead actress. Her latest film that hit commercial success was the 2018 DC movie ‚ÄúAquaman‚Äù, where she co-starred alongside Jason Momoa as Mera, the Atlantean Queen. Johnny and Amber first ignited a spark between them when they starred together in the 2011 comedy-drama film, The Rum Diary. The on-screen love story between the two has quickly travelled to real life.

In 2021, the 50 million dollar lawsuit has progressed in court, and there has been evidence that are springing out here and there that are helpful to the case of the former couple, including the recorded phone call where Despite all the evidence, since the lawsuit has not yet reached its final stage, Johnny is still currently enduring the blow of this predicament to his career, as it was also announced by Disney that Depp was relieved of his role as Jack Sparrow, one of his most famous roles in history.

As Amber Heard‚Äôs new movie, Aquaman 2, is about to be released by next year under the same production company that fired Johnny, the whole world of the internet is outraged. Because of this, the former couple‚Äôs divorce that happened in 2016 and has been finalized in 2017 still remains to be a hot topic during these days. Every now and then, new information and updates are surfacing about the couple, new evidences circulate as well, so it‚Äôs a little impossible for them not to hit the headlines all the time. In fact, Amber Heard even dropped some huge news just a couple of months ago.

That‚Äôs all for today, we hope you enjoyed that video, and if you agree that Johnny and Amber‚Äôs divorce counts as the worst, hit that like and subscribe button and smash that notification bell for more videos like this.

snippet.title: Deposition of Andrews Stalker played in Court
snippet.description:
(1 Mar 2016) FOR CLEAN VERSION SEE STORY NUMBER: 2081728

A man who stalked and secretly shot nude videos of sportscaster and TV host Erin Andrews says the plan was to sell the recordings because he needed the money.
A recorded deposition of Michael David Barrett was played Monday for jurors during Andrews' civil trial in Nashville, Tennessee. She is suing Barrett and a hotel owner and operator for $75 million (USD).
Barrett said he posted the recordings online after celebrity gossip website TMZ refused to buy it. The only reason he picked Andrews was because she was popular and he saw that she was trending on Yahoo, he said.
Barrett spent 2 1/2 years in federal prison after he admitted to renting hotel rooms next to the Andrews three times and shooting nude videos of her in Nashville and Columbus, Ohio, and posting them on the Internet.
Andrews has sued Barrett and the owner and manager of the Marriott at Vanderbilt. The Nashville hotel is a franchise.
The hotel companies say Barrett is solely to blame and he alone should be held responsible.

snippet.title: Deposition of Convicted Killer Dr. Adam Frasch, by Mentour Lawyer, months before his trial (1 of 2)
snippet.description:
The case featured in the Investigation Discovery show "American Monster" - Episode "Once a Princess" - regarding the murder of Samira Frasch.
Here I explain my goals at this deposition: https://youtu.be/CLCf4a28uQ8
 
The victim was his estranged wife, Samira Frasch. She was murdered at her home on February 22, 2014.  First he hit her in the head and broke her skull, then as she was unconscious or dying, he finished off the job by putting her in the cold swimming pool - as this would also make it difficult to determine the time of death (remember, he is a doctor).  This deposition was limited in scope.  
Mr. Cummings and Mr. Taylor, his criminal defense attorneys, limited the questions I could ask - and instructed him to plead the fifth to anything close to the murder.  Still a worthy watch!
I took this deposition while representing a homeowner's association in a wrongful death suit filed by the personal representative of the estate of Samira Frasch.

snippet.title: Body Language Analyst REACTS to the Cecil Hotel Manager's MORBID Nonverbal Communication Pt. 1 | 43
snippet.description:
By now, most of us have watched the new Netflix documentary centered around the passing of Cecil Hotel resident, Elisa Lam. The doc "Crime Scene" set out to shed light on the mystery of Lam's untimely passing, but in doing so, pushed many people to question the story even further. One aspect of suspicion is the behavior of the hotel manager, Amy Price. During the documentary, her nonverbal communication strikes many as very odd. Due to popular request, I have decided to look into the case myself and offer my opinion as to why everyone is so suspicious of the manager of the infamous Cecil Hotel.

snippet.title: At libel trial, Depp blasts Amber Heard's 'sick' abuse claim
snippet.description:
(7 Jul 2020) AT LIBEL TRIAL, DEPP BLASTS AMBER HEARD'S 'SICK' ABUSE CLAIM
Johnny Depp said Tuesday that his ex-wife Amber Heard had made ‚Äúsick‚Äù claims of abuse and falsely branded him a monster, as the actor testified in a U.K. libel case that hinges on who was the aggressor in the celebrity couple‚Äôs violent, toxic relationship 
¬†¬†
Depp is suing British tabloid The Sun over an April 2018 story headlined ‚ÄúPotty - How can JK Rowling be ‚Äògenuinely happy‚Äô casting wife beater Johnny Depp in the new Fantastic Beasts film?‚Äù
¬†¬†
The ‚ÄúPirates of the Caribbean‚Äù star strongly denies Heard's claims that he assaulted her during their tempestuous marriage, and sued The Sun's publisher, News Group Newspapers, and its executive editor, Dan Wootton.
¬†¬†
‚ÄúThese sick claims are totally untrue,‚Äù Depp said in a written witness statement, adding that Heard's allegations hurt his career and had ‚Äúbeen a constant issue in my casting.‚Äù
¬†¬†
A three-week trial over his libel claims opened Tuesday. The trial is one of the first to be held in person since Britain began to lift its coronavirus lockdown.
¬†¬†
Depp entered the witness box of the wood-paneled courtroom wearing a dark suit and tie, and began by taking the court oath and giving his full name: John Christopher Depp II.
¬†¬†
He told the court that Heard had ‚Äúsaid to the world that she was in fear of her life from me, and I had been this horrible monster, if you will. Which was not the case.‚Äù
¬†¬†
Depp, 57, and Heard, 34, met on the set of the 2011 comedy ‚ÄúThe Rum Diary‚Äù and married in Los Angeles in February 2015. They divorced in 2017, and now bitterly accuse one another of abuse.
¬†¬†
Depp and Heard arrived by separate entrances at the neo-Gothic court building. Both wore face coverings over their noses and mouths as they arrived. Proceedings have been spread over several courtrooms to allow for social distancing.
¬†¬†
While Heard isn't on trial, the case is also a showdown between the former spouses, who accuse each other of being controlling, violent and untruthful. It is set to put the two performers‚Äô complex private lives under a microscope.
¬†¬†
The Sun's defense relies on Heard's allegations of 14 incidents of violence by Depp between 2013 and 2016, in locations including Los Angeles, Australia, Japan, the Bahamas and a chartered jet. He denies them all and says Heard, an actress and model, attacked him with items including a drink can and a cigarette. He also claims that on one occasion Heard or one of her friends defecated on his bed.
¬†¬†
In written witness statements, Depp said that in Australia in 2015 Heard severed the tip of his finger by hurling a vodka bottle at him. A photo of the bloody digit was included with his witness statement.
¬†¬†
Depp claimed that on another occasion, Heard repeatedly punched him in the face on a private jet, forcing him to spend the flight locked in the plane‚Äôs bathroom.
¬†¬†
‚ÄúRage-filled violent incidents on planes were common with Amber,‚Äù he said in the written statement.
¬†¬†
Describing one incident in which Heard claims he hit her, Depp said the opposite was true.
¬†¬†
‚ÄúAs things tended to do, (it) escalated and got physical, ending with a bit of assault. Ms. Heard struck me,‚Äù he said.
¬†¬†
He painted himself as a peacemaker who tried to remove himself from conflicts "before things got out of hand.‚Äù
¬†¬†
In a written statement, Depp alleged that Heard was ‚Äúa calculating, diagnosed borderline personality; she is sociopathic; she is a narcissist; and she is completely emotionally dishonest." 
¬†¬†
¬†¬†
Heard alleges that Depp was prone to drink- and drug-fueled violent rages.
¬†¬†
¬†¬†
¬†¬†
¬†¬†
¬†¬†
¬†¬†
¬†¬†
¬†¬†
¬†¬†
¬†¬†

He was fired shortly after the incident and pleaded no contest to a simple battery charge, according to court records.

Psychopathy is a neuropsychiatric disorder marked by deficient emotional responses, lack of empathy, and poor behavioral controls, commonly resulting in persistent antisocial deviance and criminal behavior. Accumulating research suggests that psychopathy follows a developmental trajectory with strong genetic influences, and which precipitates deleterious effects on widespread functional networks, particularly within paralimbic regions of the brain. While traditional therapeutic interventions commonly administered in prisons and forensic institutions have been notoriously ineffective at combating these outcomes, alternative strategies informed by an understanding of these specific neuropsychological obstacles to healthy development, and which target younger individuals with nascent symptoms of psychopathy are more promising. 

This video features interviews with Chris Watts, Erin Caffey, Robert Durst, Darlie Routier, Richard Ramirez, Colonel Russel Williams and many more. This video is to help with mental health awareness.

The Behavior Panel is a group made up of the world's top body language and behavior experts, Mark Bowden, Scott Rouse, Greg Hartley, and Chase Hughes. Together they analyze the body language and behavior displayed in videos in the public interest. The Behavior Panel is a non-partisan group, looking to educate and entertain the public with their interest and expertise in nonverbal communication, body language, deception detection, interrogation, and resistance to interrogation. By looking at the gestures, facial expressions, micro-expressions, and context around what people say, this group of nonverbal behavior experts reveals the possible truth and deceptions. Amber Heard arrived at a scheduled deposition at 10:00 on Saturday in Los Angeles, as part of an ongoing and increasingly messy divorce with Johnny Depp.

Amber, aged 30, has accused Johnny Depp of domestic violence, and filed for divorce from the actor on May 25, two days later, she filed a domestic violence restraining order against Depp.

The actress flew into Los Angeles on Friday night after telling the judge that she couldn‚Äôt make the deposition scheduled for earlier that day due to an ‚Äúemergency‚Äù that prevented her from catching her flight on time.

A week ago she showed up for a deposition, but according to TMZ, refused to enter the conference room where lawyers and videographer were present.

The actress allegedly cried and screamed, and refused to submit to questioning.

snippet.title: Jeep Fire & Wrongful Death Case: Deposition of Former Jeep Executive about Gas Tank Location and Re
snippet.description:
We traveled to the Florida coast to take the deposition of this former executive, who worked for Fiat Chrysler Automobiles for many years and retired just after the recall of the Jeep Grand Cherokees and Jeep Liberties.  He had been involved in the decisionmaking about the Jeep "recall" that had to be done because the gas tanks were getting crushed in rear impact.  He was a high-ranking adviser to Chairman and CEO Sergio Marchionne, who made the ultimate decision regarding trailer hitches.

Jeep manufactured and sold millions of SUVs with gas tanks located in the extreme rear of the vehicle, behind the rear axle and right next to the plastic "bumper."  These gas tanks are exposed to rear impact, like the gas tanks on the 1970s-era Ford Pinto.  When these Jeeps get rear-ended, the plastic gas tanks can rupture, spraying gasoline on the roadway and on both vehicles.  If the gasoline catches fire and the people can't escape in time, the occupants the Jeep and the other vehicle can burn to death.

This has happened over and over again.

In 2013, the company that owns Jeep, Fiat Chrysler Automobiles ("FCA"), finally agreed to recall at least some of these Jeeps with exposed gas tanks.  But FCA did not buy the Jeeps back or move the gas tank.  Instead, FCA offered free trailer hitches to some Jeep owners.  That did not fix the problem‚Äîand FCA knew that it wouldn't.  Just two years before, an FCA executive had testified under oath that "the tow package does not protect the tank."

The Jeeps with exposed gas tanks are the 2002-2007 Jeep Liberty, 1993-2004 Jeep Grand Cherokee, 1993-2001 Jeep Cherokee, and 1987-2007 Jeep Wrangler.  Millions of these Jeeps remain on the road.

FCA has refused to take any further action.  FCA claims that thesee Jeeps are "absolutely safe."  In our pending litigation against FCA over these Jeep fires, FCA denies any wrongdoing.  FCA refuses declines to accept any responsibility for the hundreds of Jeep fires.

For more about Jeep fires and explosions, visit https://butlerfirm.com/jeep-fires-explosions/

For more about wrongful death cases, visit https://butlerfirm.com/georgia-wrongful-death-statute-explained/

We‚Äôd love to hear what you think!  It helps our clients if people watch these depositions and leave comments, because that helps us to know what jurors will take away from the depositions, and what questions jurors will have after watching them.  So please feel free to comment with your thoughts (good or bad) and let us know what other questions you wish we‚Äôd asked.  That‚Äôs why we post these depositions to YouTube.

For More Information on Wrongful Death Cases Visit:
https://butlerfirm.com/georgia-wrongful-death-statute-explained/
https://butlerfirm.com/georgia-wrongful-death-lawyers/wrongful-death-faqs/

snippet.title: Markeith Loyd | Interrogation of a Cop Killer
snippet.description:
On December 13, 2016, Markeith Loyd shot and killed his pregnant girlfriend, Sade Dixon and her unborn child. Loyd also shot Dixon's brother, Ronald Stewart, however Stewart survived, and along with other family members immediately identified Loyd as the person responsible. Based upon their testimony, Detective Brian Savelli of the Orange County Sheriff's Office obtained an arrest warrant charging Markeith Loyd with First Degree Murder. OCSO released Loyd's name and driver's license photograph to local media the day after the homicide, asking for assistance from the community.

On January 9, 2017, at approximately 7:15 am, a witness was shopping inside a Walmart store located at 3101 W. Princeton Street. While waiting to pay at register #2 , a black male wearing a black shirt with the word "SECURITY" on the front, stood behind her with his cart. The witness knew Markeith Loyd by name and face and was aware of his outstanding warrant, and  immediately recognized the customer behind her as Markeith Loyd.

As she paid, the witness spotted Orlando Police Sergeant Debra Clayton exiting the store. She had just purchased several small items from register #18 and was walking towards the north exit of the store adjacent to the produce section. The witness exited the store through the same door and approached Sergeant Clayton, informing her of Loyd's presence in the store.

Sergeant Clayton requested emergency radio traffic for an attempt to contact a possible homicide suspect. Eight seconds later, Officer Brandon Thornton, a member of her patrol squad, broke from his call and began traveling to her location. OPD Communications then established emergency radio traffic on the, "Emergency North" channel with responding units as well as Sergeant Clayton switching over to this channel. Units on the emergency channel began asking Sergeant Clayton for her exact location.

Fifty seconds into the call, Sergeant Clayton stated, "I guess we're looking for a Markeith. He's walking out the door right now. I guess he was involved in shooting with a pregnant female. I am at the first entrance." At one minute, fourteen seconds, she transmitted, "Foot pursuit!" followed by the sounds of three gunshots in the background. That was her last radio transmission. Dispatcher Patricia Monahan is heard asking, "B20, you 10-4?" But Sergeant Clayton was dead. And Loyd had managed to escape.

On January 17, 2017, members of the U.S. Marshals Fugitive Investigative Unit located Markeith Loyd in an abandoned house at 1157 Lescot Lane in Orlando's Carver Shores neighborhood. Loyd was observed dropping two handguns from the window of what was later determined to be the bedroom directly south of the entry door. Loyd then complied with commands and crawled on his stomach from the entry door to awaiting officers where he was placed under arrest. Loyd was wearing an American Body Armor (ABA) level IIIA bullet-resistant vest is at the time of his arrest, rated to stop all handgun ammunition commonly used by law enforcement. The firearms would remain on the ground where they had been dropped until a search warrant for the residence was executed later that evening. After being secured he was transported to the Orlando Police Headquarters for interrogation by Detectives Danny Garcia-Pagan and Pete Cadiz.

This is the interrogation of Markeith Loyd.

24:55 OPD Det. Pete Cadiz & Danny Garcia-Pagan
28:18 Interrogation begins
1:09:50 "In the street, you're nothing"
1:14:38 Photographs
1:29:50 Medical assistance provided
1:48:50 Bunny suit (a portion of this is silent)
1:51:34 Audio is back

About The Doctors:

The Doctors is an Emmy award-winning daytime talk show hosted by ER physician Dr. Travis Stork, plastic surgeon Dr. Andrew Ordon and OB-GYN Dr. Nita Landry.

The Doctors helps you understand the latest health headlines, such as the ice bucket challenge for ALS and the Ebola outbreak; delivers exclusive interviews with celebrities dealing with health issues, such as Lamar Odom, Teen Mom star Farrah Abraham, reality stars Honey Boo Boo and Mama June and activist Chaz Bono; brings you debates about health and safety claims from agricultural company Monsanto and celebrities such as Jenny McCarthy; and shows you the latest gross viral videos and explains how you can avoid an emergency situation. snippet.title: McDonough v. Murguido; full deposition of Murguido
snippet.description:
Full unedited video provided by the certified court videographer.

Video deposition taken of Homestead Police Officer Alejandro Murguido on October 11th, 2017.

Pay attention to the inverted cross he has pinned to his shirt. Was he trying to send a message?

We talk about two incidents. One Murguido claims happened on July 27th, 2012. This incident never happened. 

The second incident occurred on October 29th, 2012. We had a consensual conversation, then I left and he chased me down. A recording of the conversation is here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GUS5EzZpwEg

Murguido file a false stalking injunction against me on February 28th, 2013. On the second page of the document you can see his statement of the conversation in the first paragraph of his narrative. His deposition answers nearly perfectly followed this:
https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/3227642-12-First-Stalking-Injunction.html

What is most obvious as to Murguido's perjury in deposition and in his sworn statement(s) is that: 1) He never asked me to leave even a single time; 2) I never said I was going to get him and he would see; 3) I never threatened him other than to file a complaint; 4) I never said that I was following him around; 5) I never whistled at him; 6) He never asked me if he was in a police car; 7) He never claimed that under certain situation he was allowed to run through stop signs or speed; 8) I never said I didn't care that he was in a police car; 9) I never said anything about his driving habits in his neighborhood; and 10) He never told me to go to IA and file a complaint if I had a problem.

It will be interesting to see him on the witness stand as his credibility is impeached.

snippet.title: Extraordinary Modes of Fossil Preservation
snippet.description: Most of us are familiar with fossils, ranging from invertebrates like shells, bugs, and ammonites, to giant vertebrates like dinosaurs. The vast majority are preserved through permineralization, where groundwater percolates through pore spaces and deposits minerals within them. But not always! In this talk, Jon Noad presents some very unusual and truly spectacular examples of fossilization, ranging from replacement by opal and various metals including gold; to preservation of internal organs as casts; fossil feathers, nests, and eggs; three-dimensional specimens, and more.

snippet.description:
The Dropout - Reframing the Narrative
================================================================
This week, Elizabeth Holmes returns to the stand, presenting herself as a confident CEO with a noble mission who also naively took experts at their word. She meticulously details how she built her business -- even admitting to having doctored those pharmaceutical documents -- but implies over and over again that she relied on information given to her by scientists, doctors and board members to solidify her understanding of where her company stood. Will it be enough to convince a jury that she had no intent to defraud investors?

snippet.description: Dopo tre anni, Johnny Depp e Amber Heard sono apparsi in pubblico nello stesso luogo. Entrambi infatti sono stati chiamati a testimoniare all'alta corte di Londra in merito al processo per diffamazione dell'anno, quello della star di "Pirati dei Caraibi" contro il tabloid britannico "Sun" e la sua ex moglie e attrice texana Amber Heard. Depp infatti era stato accusato di aver picchiato la moglie mentre era ubriaco. Johnny Depp e Amber Heard si sono presentati senza mascherina ma con il volto coperto da dei foulard: nero quello dell'attore, che aveva un completo scuro, e rosso con dei pois quello dell'attrice, che indossava un abito nero.

snippet.title: Reckless Driving & Delivery Case: Deposition of Jimmy John's Corporate Representative
snippet.description:
When you litigate against a large company, it's not always clear who you should talk to in order to get the company's official position.  A low-level employee isn't high-ranking enough to speak for the company, and the President or CEO might not know anything about your specific case, or might be unavailable.  To handle that issue, Rule 30(b)(6) requires that, upon request, the company must choose someone to answer questions on its behalf.  Under federal law, the citation is Fed. R. Civ. P. 30(b)6), and in Georgia it's O.C.G.A. ¬ß  9-11-30(b)(6).  This deposition is of such a person, often called a "corporate representative" or "30(b)6) designee." 

We handled a reckless driving & punitive damages case against Jimmy Johns in which a delivery person (a bicyclist) crashed into our client (a pedestrian), knocking him down and breaking his arm so severely that a plate and ten screws had to be inserted.  This video shows our deposition of Jimmy John's corporate representative.

We tried the case in the State Court of Fulton County in Atlanta, Georgia.  The jury returned a verdict of $167,000 for our client.  https://butlerfirm.com/two-successful-personal-injury-verdicts-in-three-business-days/

We‚Äôd love to hear what you think!  It helps our clients if people watch these depositions and leave comments, because that helps us to know what jurors will take away from the depositions, and what questions jurors will have after watching them.  So please feel free to comment with your thoughts (good or bad) and let us know what other questions you wish we‚Äôd asked.  That‚Äôs why we post these depositions to YouTube.

snippet.title: Amber Heard's Sister EXPOSES Her For Lying!
snippet.description:
Amber Heard's Sister EXPOSES Her For Lying! 
Since Johnny Depp's attorneys provided video recordings of his ex-wife being abusive against her in his libel suit towards a British tabloid, Amber Heard's sister denied lying before a London judge. On Thursday night, his legal team got the video from a "confidential" source, just hours after Whitney Henriquez testified in court that she had never been targeted by Heard and was not afraid of her.

Depp, 57, is suing News Group Newspapers, the publisher of The Sun, and Dan Wootton, the newspaper's executive editor, for calling him a "wife be*ter" in an April 2018 post. Depp has testified in court that he was the one who was harassed by Heard and that she has a history of violence against him.

snippet.title: Impeachment trial of President Trump | Jan. 22, 2020 (FULL LIVE STREAM)
snippet.description:
After a debate on the rules of the trial, opening arguments start Jan. 22 in the Senate. After opening arguments, senators will have 16 hours to ask questions in writing. Chief Justice John G. Roberts Jr. will read the questions out loud, and the appropriate side ‚Äî defense or prosecution ‚Äî can answer them. 

President Trump was impeached by the House of Representatives in December for abuse of power and obstruction of Congress. Impeachment does not mean that the president has been removed from office. In the next phase, the Senate must hold a trial to make that determination. A Senate impeachment trial has happened only two other times in American history and once in the modern era. At the center of the Democrats‚Äô case is that Trump sought to withhold military assistance and an Oval Office meeting until Ukraine announced investigations into former vice president Joe Biden and his son.

Watch the debate on Jan. 21 on the rules of the trial: https://youtu.be/yz_J8sfZVEE. Read more: https://wapo.st/30KZknd. Subscribe to The Washington Post on YouTube: https://wapo.st/2QOdcqK

snippet.title: Was Ted Bundy Sorry? Final Interview Body Language Analysis
snippet.description:
SAVE MONEY ON YOUR EDUCATION
Observe is partnered with the Emotional Intelligence Academy in the UK to offer discounts of 10%-50% on your education including a fully accredited Master's Degree! Just follow the link: https://www.eiagroup.com/observe

Theodore Robert Bundy was born on November 24, 1946. While he claimed he had an overall happy and average childhood, many describe Bundy as having a difficult childhood. He spent his early years with his maternal grandparents, who raised him as their son. Bundy was said to have thought his mother was his sister, according to a prison psychologist who once interviewed Bundy, in the documentary "The Ted Bundy Tapes." He apparently didn't find out who his birth mother was until later in life. Along with this, a forensic psychologist and FBI and law enforcement consultant stated that Bundy exhibited signs of conduct disorder as a child.

This was further amplified as a young Bundy began to avidly view violent pornography. He stated in his final interview that he felt the need to take in more extreme content to give himself the same feeling until he finally realized what he had to do to take it to the next level.

While his first attack occurred early in 1974, his first killing occurred on or around February 1st of 1974 from that point on through the year 1978, according to his own confession, he killed, kidnapped, and assaulted more than 30 women in seven states, while escaping from prison twice. After his final arrest in 1979, Bundy insisted on acting as his own attorney and even cross-examined witnesses during his trial. However, he was found guilty of murder and was sentenced to death via electric chair.

Over the next ten years, legalities would play out. Bundy even was married during his imprisonment and had a child. However, he was later divorced and was executed by electric chair at 7:06 a.m. on January 24, 1989, at Florida State Prison in Starke, Florida.

Theodore Robert Bundy was born on November 24, 1946. While he claimed he had an overall happy and average childhood, many describe Bundy as having a difficult childhood. He spent his early years with his maternal grandparents, who raised him as their son. Bundy was said to have thought his mother was his sister, according to a prison psychologist who once interviewed Bundy, in the documentary "The Ted Bundy Tapes." He apparently didn't find out who his birth mother was until later in life. Along with this, a forensic psychologist and FBI and law enforcement consultant stated that Bundy exhibited signs of conduct disorder as a child.

This was further amplified as a young Bundy began to avidly view violent pornography. He stated in his final interview that he felt the need to take in more extreme content to give himself the same feeling until he finally realized what he had to do to take it to the next level.

While his first attack occurred early in 1974, his first killing occurred on or around February 1st of 1974 from that point on through the year 1978, according to his own confession, he killed, kidnapped, and assaulted more than 30 women in seven states, while escaping from prison twice. After his final arrest in 1979, Bundy insisted on acting as his own attorney and even cross-examined witnesses during his trial. However, he was found guilty of murder and was sentenced to death via electric chair.

Over the next ten years, legalities would play out. Bundy even was married during his imprisonment and had a child. However, he was later divorced and was executed by electric chair at 7:06 a.m. on January 24, 1989, at Florida State Prison in Starke, Florida.

snippet.title: Dr Phil Gets Very Annoyed By This 13 Year Old
snippet.description:
Dr Phil Gets Very Annoyed With This 13 Year Old Kid! 

Dr. Phil is an American talk show created by Oprah Winfrey and the host Phil McGraw. After McGraw's success with his segments on The Oprah Winfrey Show, Dr. Phil debuted on September 16, 2002. On both shows McGraw offers advice in the form of "life strategies" from his life experience as a clinical and forensic psychologist.[2]

The show is in syndication throughout the United States and a number of other countries. Its tenth season premiered on September 12, 2011. Occasional prime time specials have aired on CBS. The program has been nominated for a Daytime Emmy Award every year since 2004. Since September 2008, Dr. Phil has been broadcast in HDTV with a revamped look and a new theme written and performed by McGraw's son, Jordan.

The executive producers are Phil McGraw and showrunner Oprah Winfrey. It is a production of Peteski Productions and distributed by CBS Television Distribution. Harpo Productions co-produced the series until 2010, with Paramount Domestic Television and its successor, CBS Paramount Domestic Television, serving as secondary co-producers until 2007. It was originally distributed by King World Productions.

The program is recorded before a live studio audience in Stage 29 on the Paramount Pictures lot in Hollywood, California. On October 25, 2018, it was announced that Dr. Phil had been renewed for four additional seasons, taking the show to May 2023, or the end of its 21st season.

snippet.title: Impeachment trial of President Trump | Jan. 27, 2020 (FULL LIVE STREAM)
snippet.description:
The House managers wrapped up their arguments against President Trump on Jan. 24. Trump‚Äôs team, including lawyers Pat Cipollone and Jay Sekulow, now has 24 hours to present their case. After Trump‚Äôs lawyers conclude their presentation, senators will have an opportunity to submit questions to both sides in writing. Following that, debate will turn to whether to call witnesses and subpoena documents.

Trump was impeached by the House of Representatives in December for abuse of power and obstruction of Congress. Impeachment does not mean that the president has been removed from office. In the next phase, the Senate must hold a trial to make that determination. A Senate impeachment trial has happened only two other times in American history and once in the modern era. At the center of the Democrats‚Äô case is that Trump sought to withhold military assistance and an Oval Office meeting until Ukraine announced investigations into former vice president Joe Biden and his son.

snippet.title: LIVE: Johnny Depp libel trial against ‚ÄòThe Sun‚Äô starts at London High Court: stakeout
snippet.description:
Ruptly is live outside the High Court in London on Tuesday, July 7, as the actor Johnny Depp and Amber Heard are expected to attend the first day of the libel trial against the publishers of The Sun.
 
The trial, in which Johnny Depp is bringing a lawsuit against The Sun newspaper, is related to a 2018 article claiming he was abusive to his ex-wife Amber Heard. A court order published on Saturday said that Amber could be in court for Depp's testimony.
 
The libel trial was originally scheduled to begin on March 23, but was later postponed because of the coronavirus outbreak.‚Äã

snippet.title: Johnny Depp makes rare red carpet appearance amid Amber Heard drama
snippet.description:
Title: Johnny Depp Returns To Red Carpet, Soon Surrounded By Die-Hard Fans

Read More Stories Here: www.haveitalldaily.com 

Description: 
Johnny Depp is the centre of attention once again for all the right reasons as he attended a screening of his latest film at the 47th Deauville Film Festival in France of Sunday. After numerous bad press including the recent libel case, die hard fans proved they will always have Depp‚Äôs back as they gathered for a glimpse of Depp in northwestern France. 

Depp was promoting City of Lies which is based on an unsolved murder of '90s rap giants Tupac Shakur and the Notorious B.I.G, out of competition at this year's ceremony.

Depp looked happy to be back on the red carpet but also excited to spend time with fans as he stopped to talk to some giving out autographs ahead of the screening. 

This is a true turning point for Depp and may be exactly what he needs to put the recent bad publicity behind him though only time will tell.

snippet.title: Serial Cop Impersonator Jeremy Dewitte's latest arrest in Florida Part 2 of 2 The Sit Down Interview
snippet.description:
@Cop Watch obtained body worn camera from Orange County Sheriff's Department located in Florida. This is a 2.5 hour interview with Dewitte with Orange County Sheriff's office after his arrest. 

Dewitte was arrested during a traffic stop on March 23rd, 2021. Deputies say he was dressed as a police officer and carrying a weapon on his motorcycle. Orange County sheriff‚Äôs deputies said they spotted Jeremy Dewitte around 9:45 p.m. while traveling eastbound on Interstate 4.
 
The Orange County Sheriff‚Äôs Office said Dewitte was the rider leading the group in the far left travel lane of the highway. Dewitte was the only one openly carrying a firearm, which is a violation of state law, according to the Sheriff‚Äôs office.

After this interview concealed weapons charges were dropped against Dewitte on March 24th, 2021.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Drunken Tantrum ‚Äì On Tape! | TMZ TV
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp went crazy on Amber Heard in their kitchen, throwing a wine bottle and glass ... and she videotaped it. 
We're told the video was shot months before the May 21 incident in which Amber claims Johnny struck her.
Amber asks Johnny if he drank a bottle of wine and tries to calm him down. She says she was sorry for something although she was not specific.   
Johnny isn't having it, and appears out of control. After throwing the glass and bottle, you see him swiping at Amber's phone ... trying to get it from her.
